title: Miles Morales: Spider-Man #2
body:
I dig the dynamic between Rhino and Miles. They have different strengths and weaknesses that play off each other well. I’d honestly be ok if they really kept this team up going for a while. I think they can get a lot of millage out of this. Plus I haven’t really read a ton of stories that explored Rhino, but its easily to tell he’s got some depth to him. They can really open that up here and use that as a teaching moment for Miles. Help them both grow. Don’t know how I feel about Cap showing up. We’ll just have to wait and see. But yeah. This was a good issue. I think this new creative team will do good stuff with Miles.

-Chuck

summary: It was bound to happen sooner or later, but a winter storm has cancelled school and postponed our first Fun Fact of the year......
caption:
It was bound to happen sooner or later, but a winter storm has cancelled school and postponed our first Fun Fact of the year… So keep warm, stay inside today, and enjoy this short episode from the 1960s Spider-Man animated series titled “Trouble with Snow!” ❄️

A snowman is brought to life after being struck by an electrical cable and starts wreaking havoc on the city. Why the cable didn’t melt him is anyone’s guess, but apparently the reason he’s alive is because there are chemicals in the snow… Solves everything. ⛄

but they would've gotten married if Betty hadn't said that she wanted to marry a stable guy
summary: Anyone who minimizes Peter and Betty’s old relationship, be it by saying Gwen was his first love, by having Peter say he only...
body: Anyone who minimizes Peter and Betty’s old relationship, be it by saying Gwen was his first love, by having Peter say he only had a crush on her because she was the first person who was nice to him outside of his aunt and uncle, or by having Betty dismiss their relationship as “a long time ago”, say he wasn’t there when his brother died (when he had actually tracked her down when she left the city to help her with it) and talk about the time he went out as Spider-Man when he had a debilitating illness as “he had a cruch on me and I was fond of him” has a micro dick energy.

summary: imagine mcu peter just calmly standing in tonys lab hands on his hips, every single inch within a 15 foot radius covered in...
question: imagine mcu peter just calmly standing in tonys lab hands on his hips, every single inch within a 15 foot radius covered in exploded webbing and when tony walks in he looks him in the eyes and goes "several bad choices have led me to this moment" and sounds perfectly content in a tone that suggests nothing has happened
answer:
Oh my gosh I love this

Okay but every time something small happens, like his webbing shooting everywhere or when he knocks his toe against the edge of a table (oof), he just stares into the distance and says is a serious tone: “several bad choices have led me to this moment” or “I now know why Jesus died. To get away from our shit”

BUT when something major happens, like him getting shot or getting attacked by monsters in all directions, Peter just. He just contently alerts someone of his situation or starts thinking about unnecessary things like: “oh hey mr stark wHHHaaaAtsss poppin? Not drugs I hope hAHAH anywayyy I got stabbed you wanna go get some doughtnuts though (dough HAHA I’m hilarious)??” or “wait wait wait shut up for a moment monsters, I think I know the answer to question 7 on my bio worksheet I need to write it down hold up” (honestly this one fits peter b parker more hhh)
